<HEAD>Dollar Up, Stocks Slip</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Stands as 2nd Ld-Writethru to f0292, AM-Japan-Markets</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar rose against the Japanese yen in
Tokyo on Friday, while stock prices declined for the first time in
a week.
   After opening at 126.07 yen, 0.39 yen above Thursday's close,
the dollar generally remained steady. It closed at 126.11 yen, up
0.43 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues lost 47.82 points, or 0.17 percent, to close the
day at 27,821.54.
   The volume on the market's first section was estimated to be a
heavy 2 billion shares.
