<HEAD>Ohio GOP Adopts Rule Requiring Equal Female Delegate
Representation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Women will comprise half of Ohio's
Republican Party delegation to the 1992 GOP national convention,
after the party implemented a rule change over the objections of
some men.
   The Republican State Central and Executive Committee on Thursday
adopted a rule that for the first time requires Republican
presidential candidates to include equal numbers of men and women
on their delegate slates in order to qualify for the ballot.
   The rule change stirred debate among the 42-member GOP
committee, which is itself equally represented by one man and one
woman from each of the state's congressional districts.
