<2ND_LINE>PM-Multiple Valedictorians,0226</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>14 Share Honors As High School Class Valedictorian</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELLEFONTAINE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This year's valedictorian at
Bellefontaine High School is Elizabeth Hendershod _ and 13 others
who finished the academic year with perfect grades.
   The 14, who racked up 4.0 grade-point averages in their senior
year at the western Ohio high school, will be honored Sunday when
the school awards diplomas Sunday to its graduating class of 185.
   ``This is indeed a unique situation,'' said schools
Superintendent Robert W. Carter. ``I've never seen anything like in
all my 33 years in education.''
   ``It makes us look like we're grading on a very easy kind of
basis,'' said the school's principal, George Harris. ``But these
are the same standards that we've always had. This is an extremely
unusual group of kids who just happen to be in the same class.''
   Tammy Watson, a valedictorian and class secretary, credited
``tremendous unity'' within the class for the high success rate.
``We work together and help each other to reach higher goals.''
   Hendershod said intense competition was involved.
   ``The fact that there were 13 other candidates helped to
motivate us,'' she said. ``We would say to ourselves, `I'm not
gonna allow that other person to get it and leave me out. If that
person can get it, I can too.' ''
