<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Arafat-Shultz     06-03 0281</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Arafat-Shultz,0289</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>PLO Leader Says Shultz `Moving Round in Vicious Circle'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ABU DHABI, United Arab Emirates (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   PLO leader Yasser Arafat
said Secretary of State George Shultz will not succeed in reaching
peace in the Middle East unless his plan includes the Palestine
Liberation Organization.
   Arafat said Shultz, who headed to Egypt today to start his third
shuttle to promote a regional peace plan, is ``moving round in a
vicious circle.''
   In an interview with Abu Dhabi television broadcast late
Thursday, Arafat said the plan Shultz is promoting ``excludes the
Palestinian nation and its legitimate representative, the PLO.''
   ``He will not succeed with his plan because it runs counter to
the U.N. resolutions that recognize the Palestinian nation's right
to an independent state on its national soil,'' Arafat said.
   The PLO leader said the Shultz mission was designed ``to protect
Israel from the earthquake caused by the uprising and the
steadfastness in south Lebanon.''
   Arafat was referring to the uprising by Palestinians in the
Israeli-occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip that began Dec. 8.
Palestinians in south Lebanon, which borders Israel, mount
operations against the Israelis.
   Arafat gave the interview during a two-day visit to the United
Arab Emirates. He is touring Arab capitals before an Arab summit
June 7 in Algiers, Algeria, on the Palestinian uprising.
   The PLO has rejected the Shultz plan because it reportedly
envisages only a limited self-rule on the West Bank and Gaza Strip
in an initial phase and does not recognize the PLO, which is
fighting a guerrilla war for a Palestinian homeland, as the leader
of the Palestinians.
   The plan calls for an international peace conference and
negotiations on an Palestinian homeland.
</TEXT>
