<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Missile Launch, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0603,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Air Force Launches Successful Minuteman Missile Test, Officials
Say</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs 4th graf with one graf to update with missile hitting
target.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>VANDENBERG AIR FORCE BASE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Air Force
successfully launched an unarmed Minuteman 3 missile today in a
test of its ability to deliver multiple nuclear warheads to distant
targets, officials said.
   The intercontinental ballistic missile was launched at 6:28
a.m., aimed at Kwajalein Atoll near the Marshall Islands in the
western Pacific Ocean, said Airman 1st Class Ann-Marie Townsend.
   ``The purpose of the launch is to test and evaluate how well the
missile operates,'' said Master Sgt. Bruce Zielsdorf.
   The missile's payload landed on the atoll target about 4,200
miles away roughly 30 minutes after launch, Zielsdorf said.
   It was the 132nd such launch in a series of Strategic Air
Command tests of the Minuteman 3, and the 469th Minuteman launch
overall, Zielsdorf said.
