<HEAD>President On Sick Leave</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Karoly Nemeth, who recently
was demoted from two key political posts, has gone on sick leave,
the state news agency MTI reported Friday.
   The agency said Nemeth has been on sick leave since Wednesday
and his duties will be performed by Vice President Rezsoe
Trautmann. It did not give any further details.
   At the end of the Communist Party conference May 20-22, Nemeth
was dropped from the Communist Party's 108-member Central
Committee. He later lost his post in the ruling Politburo when it
shrank from 13 to 11 members.
   Nemeth, 66, was named president in June 1987.
