<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Obit-Seiferheld     06-03 0132</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Seiferheld,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Historian And AP Correspondent Dead At 37</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASUNCION, Paraguay (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Historian and journalist Alfredo
Seiferheld, correspondent for The Associated Press in Asuncion
since 1982, died Friday of cancer, his family said. He was 37.
   Seiferheld also worked for Time magazine and was a journalist
with the Asuncion newspaper ABC Color before it was closed in 1984
by the government of President Gen. Alfredo Stroessner for
allegedly publishing ``subversive'' articles.
   A graduate in history from the University of Sorbonne in Paris,
Seiferheld wrote several books, including ``The Asylum Of Peron,''
``The Fall Of Federico Chavez,'' ``Jews In Paraguay'' and
``Political-Military Conversations.''
   Seiferheld was a member of the Paraguayan Academy Of History and
secretary-general of the Paraguayan Institute of Geo-Political
Studies.
   He is survived by his wife and three children.
</TEXT>
