<HEAD>9-year-old Wanted for Burglaries, As Victim</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said Friday they were searching
for a 9-year-old boy wanted in a string of burglaries allegedly
conducted with his 10-year-old partner.
   The boys, who lived in a hotel primarily used as a residence for
the homeless, allegedly conducted one burglary with an adult, who
is charged with sexually abusing them, police said.
   Paul Karnaugh, 30, of White Plains, was charged Wednesday with
three counts of first-degree sodomy and one count of third-degree
burglary, police said. He was jailed in lieu of $10,000 bail.
   Karnaugh was arrested after police charged the 10-year-old with
seven counts of third-degree burglary for ransacking and
vandalizing several offices, police Capt. James Harding said.
   The 10-year-old boy was in the custody of the county's Child
Protective Services at an undisclosed location. The 9-year-old boy
was being sought, Harding said. His mother and the boy frequently
spend days at a time away from the hotel, he said.
