<1ST_LINE>r f PM-OilPrices     06-03 0219</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Oil Prices,0230</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Oil Prices Close Mixed In Listless Market</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oil futures prices finished mixed after another
quiet trading session.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange Thursday, contracts for July
delivery of West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark U.S. crude,
closed at $17.65 per 42-gallon barrel, up 7 cents.
   Among July contracts for refined products, wholesale unleaded
gasoline settled down 0.23 cent at 51.51 cents a gallon, while
wholesale heating oil closed at 47.38 cents per gallon, up 0.07
cent.
   Technical factors were entirely responsible for the day's
activity, while volume remained at ``about half'' normal levels
said Stephen J. McKiernan, of the McKiernan & Co. commodities firm.
   Analysts said traders were reluctant to make large moves in the
market until they see what happens at the upcoming summer meeting
of oil ministers of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries in Vienna, Austria.
   In a Thursday announcement, a spokesman said the conference had
been postponed by three days to June 11.
   ``There is no official reason for the postponement, but most
likely the meeting was delayed because it coincided with the Arab
summit meeting in Algiers'' that starts Tuesday, the spokesman said
in Vienna.
   The OPEC ministers are expected to make another attempt at
negotiating a package of production cutbacks in order to support
prices.
</TEXT>
