<HEAD>Consumer, Wholesale Prices Up In May</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korea's consumer prices rose 0.5
percent in May compared with the previous month and and 6.5 percent
from a year ago, the Economic Planning Board reported Friday.
   The board also said wholesale prices rose 0.4 percent last month
from April and 1.9 percent from May 1987.
   The increases, which followed declines in April, were attributed
partly to hikes in wages, cooking coal and housing rentals.
   The government is attempting to keep the annual consumer and
wholesale price inflation to 4.5 percent and 3 percent respectively.
