<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Japanese     06-03 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Japanese,0195</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hitachi Posts First Earnings Gain In Three Years</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Hitachi Ltd. said Friday it managed its first gains in profits
and sales in three years in fiscal 1987 as profit jumped 39 percent
and revenue climbed 3 percent.
   Hitachi, the giant Japanese manufacturer of electronics and
electrical equipment, said its profit rose to 136.8 billion yen, or
$1.09 billion, in the fiscal year ended March 31, from 98.7 billion
yen a year earlier.
   Revenue rose to 4.98 trillion yen, or $39.8 billion, from 4.85
trillion yen a year earlier.
   The increases left Hitachi still short of its peak year of
fiscal 1984, when revenue surpassed 5 trillion yen and profit was
more than 210 billion yen.
   Hitachi attributed the gains to a continued advance in its
computer business, a recovery in semiconductors and gains from the
upswing in Japan's domestic demand. It said those offset a mediocre
showing by its heavy electrical equipment and consumer products
sectors.
   The results, which include the consolidated results of its
overseas subsidiaries, were converted into dollars at a rate of 125
yen to the dollar.
</TEXT>
