<2ND_LINE>BC-May-Florida Sale,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>May Will Sell Five-Store May Florida Chain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   May Department Stores Inc. has agreed
to sell its five-store May Florida chain to Maison
Blanche-Goudchaux of Baton Rouge, La.
   Three of the stores are in Jacksonville, one is in Orange Park
and the other store is in Daytona Beach.
   The purchase price was not disclosed.
   In a statement, May said the transaction is to be completed by
the end of July and is subject to definitive agreements and closing
conditions being negotiated.
   May Department Stores, the seventh-largest retailer in the
United States, operates 3,059 stores. Maison Blanche operates seven
department stores in Louisiana and 10 in Florida.
   The May Florida deal is the second in the past 12 months between
Maison Blanche and the St. Louis-based May Department Stores.
   Last August, May sold its 10-store Robinson's of Florida chain
to Maison Blanche.
</TEXT>
